By Joy Kaka  Abuja    –       The police on Wednesday arraigned a carpenter, Abbah Ahmed, who allegedly stole phones while celebrating the last Eid-El-Kabir. Ahmed, a resident of Mararaba, Nasarawa State,‎ appeared before a Kubwa Grade 1 Area Court, Abuja, on a two-count charge of conspiracy and theft. The accused, however, pleaded not guilty. The Prosecutor, Mr John Okpa, submitted that Ahmed and one person at large ‎conspired and stole phones worth N56, 000 from Messrs Anas Muhammed and Ibrahim Musa while they were watching a movie at the Jabi Lake Mall in Abuja in celebration of Eid-El-Kabir. He said that the conspiracy and theft occurred on Aug. 22. The prosecutor said that the accused ran away but was later arrested. He noted that the offences contravened Sections 79 and 288 of the Penal Code. The Judge, Mr Abdulwahab Mohammed, granted the accused N200, 000 bail with a surety in like sum.‎ He adjourned the case until Oct. 11 for substantive hearing.